Use the standard library
This is how to do_algebra of operator and operand:
  Remember that result is item 0 in operand
  Remember that i is 0
  Do this operator's length times:
    When i is at least operator's length, then:
      Leave the loop
    End when
    Remember that op is item i in operator
    Remember that next_value is item sum of i and 1 in operand
    When op is "+", then:
      Remember that result is sum of result and next_value
    End when
    When op is "-", then:
      Remember that result is diff of result and next_value
    End when
    When op is "*", then:
      Remember that result is product of result and next_value
    End when
    When op is "**", then:
      Remember that power is 1
      Remember that count is 0
      Do this next_value times:
        Remember that power is product of power and result
        Increase count
      End do
      Remember that result is power
    End when
    Increase i
  End do
  The answer is result
Now you know